toplevel: true
title: Globus
---



\

\

\

The Center for High Performance Computing (CHPC) supports research
computing at the University of Utah. They house cluster computing
resources consisting of over 22,000 CPU cores and 13 PB of RAID
configured spinning disks. UCGD owns just over 2,000 CPU cores and over
3 PB of disk space in CHPC\'s HIPAA Protected Environment, and we have
access to all additional CHPC resource on a pre-emptable guest basis. To
work with UCGD data you will need to apply for an account with CHPC as
well as apply for access to the Protected Environment.

\

-   [CHPC\'s Getting Started
    Documentation](https://www.chpc.utah.edu/documentation/gettingstarted.php)
-   [Get an account at
    CHPC](https://www.chpc.utah.edu/userservices/accounts.php)
-   [Get access to the Protected Environment
    (PE)](https://www.chpc.utah.edu/resources/ProtectedEnvironment.php#RequestPE)

\

[Note: collaborators should select PE
group ]**proj_UCGDCollab**[ with Mark
Yandell as PI when requesting access to the Protected environment
(PE).]

\







